{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770048888,"nonce":"/693fsTazdWXhYRm/G8DqhbnTFc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nq8To","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/127","origin":"github"},"title":"fix: simplify .gitignore to ignore entire layers/ directory","message":"## Problem\n\nThe `worktree_remove.sh` script warns about \"uncommitted changes\" even when workspace worktrees are clean, requiring `--force` flag unnecessarily.\n\n**Root Cause**:\n- Main workspace: `layers/` is a real directory (ROS2 workspaces)\n- Workspace worktrees: `layers/` is a symlink pointing back to main\n- Git sees the symlink as untracked file: `?? layers/`\n- Script's `git status --porcelain` check flags this as uncommitted change\n\n**Current State**:\n```bash\n$ .agent/scripts/worktree_remove.sh --issue 110\n⚠️  Warning: Worktree has uncommitted changes:\n\n?? layers/\n\nUse --force to remove anyway, or commit/stash your changes first.\n```\n\n## Discovery\n\n**Nothing in `layers/` is tracked by git**:\n```bash\n$ git ls-files | grep \"^layers/\"\n# (no results - all managed by vcstool)\n```\n\nCurrent `.gitignore` has granular rules:\n```\nlayers/main/*/src/\nlayers/main/*/build/\nlayers/main/*/install/\nlayers/main/*/log/\nlayers/worktrees/\n```\n\nBut nothing needs to be tracked there—all ROS2 code is pulled via vcstool from `.repos` files.\n\n## Solution\n\nSimplify `.gitignore` to ignore entire `layers/` directory:\n\n```diff\n+# Ignore entire layers directory (managed by vcstool)\n+layers/\n+\n-# Ignore ROS2 layers because they are managed by vcs and .repos files\n-# Main builds live in layers/main/\n-layers/main/*/src/\n-layers/main/*/build/\n-layers/main/*/install/\n-layers/main/*/log/\n-\n-# Ignore layer worktrees (created dynamically for task isolation)\n-# Each worktree contains target layer + symlinks to main\n-layers/worktrees/\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n- ✅ Fixes worktree removal false positive\n- ✅ Simpler `.gitignore` (1 rule vs 6)\n- ✅ Works for both main workspace and all worktrees\n- ✅ No breaking changes (nothing tracked there anyway)\n\n## Validation\n\nVerified zero files tracked in `layers/`:\n```bash\n$ git ls-files | grep \"^layers/\" | wc -l\n0\n```\n\n---\n**🤖 Reported-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}